<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98017725612611></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98017725612611><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=2&mid=98017725612611>RE: what is the best race</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=22025><span id= >Krasatha</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>32 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 22nd 3:30 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dark Elves make good Rogues, They have Hide by nature and the Sneak and Hide both on lets you walk around hidden. That's one of their advantages. I chose a DE and made it to level 8 in a shorter time than it usually takes to level, Mind you Soloing a Rogue of Any race isn't good, You should be in a full group most of the time, Bigger the group, Bigger the Exp. When you level to the point that you have all your extra stuff, Backstab, Make poison, Apply Poison,Stuff like that, You can start soloing more often.<br>&nbsp;<br>Krasatha<br>Teir'Dal Rogue<br>Follower Of No Deity<br>Empire Of The Damned</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
