<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97897351028796></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97897351028796><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=2&mid=97897351028796>RE: what is the best race</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1139><span id=Scholar>Kehvrynne</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>45 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 8th 5:06 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Discussions on this pop up on a weekly basis over at <a href=HTTP://<a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org target=_new>The" target=_new>http://www.thesafehouse.org]The</a> Safehouse</a>.  Log parsing by the scholarly-minded has shown there isn't much difference in character performance once stats hit 100.  Yeah, STR bumps up your damage a bit, but you get more of an increase out of your ATK skill than you do from STR.  In my experience weapon Procs seem to be based more on the weapon than DEX - I've some weapons which proc at least once a fight and others which hardly proc at all.  The AC increases provided by AGI are minimal (1 AC per 3AGI) and only help the Avoidance factor.  If you get hit, only item AC helps reduce the damage taken.  My STA is 75 and I've never had a problem with running out.<br><br>Essentially, for melee classes with zero casting ability, race is a role-playing choice.  Stats only matter pre-100 level.  Pick what you LIKE, not what think is going to give you the biggest edge.<br>&nbsp;<br>Thesipian Rogue of Bristlebane&lt;br&gt;<br>&lt;a href="<a href="http://i.am/amnesty/"&gt;Amnesty&lt;/a&gt;," target=_new>http://i.am/amnesty/"&gt;Amnesty&lt;/a&gt;,</a> Saryrn</td></tr>
